other_tests.procedure_name: CT Abdomen and Pelvis with Contrast
other_tests.findings: Appendix is dilated up to 11 mm with wall thickening and mild hyperemia. There is surrounding mild to moderate fat stranding and trace free fluid along the right pericolic gutter. A few scattered mesenteric lymph nodes in the right lower quadrant are likely reactive. Several subcentimeter hypodense lesions within the uterus are most likely fibroids.
